pr_body:
@edmorley / @rbillings r?

Ad-hoc run here: https://fx-test-jenkins-dev.stage.mozaws.net:8443/job/treeherder.adhoc/27/console 

A few failures, but seems consistent with current master: https://fx-test-jenkins-dev.stage.mozaws.net:8443/job/treeherder.adhoc/28/console

@VipulM-MSFT , @vturecek , @suhuruli, @samedder, @mani-ramaswamy  please review the change

Addresses #40 and points to this repo for instructions if there is version mismatch.

Updated install instructions to allow SXS install of different versions of sfctl using pipenv or containers.

Add a new decorator that can be added on each function that take times. (or for debug / development purpose)

** simple log**

        @openupgrade.logging()
        def my_function(*args):


** log every x call**

        @openupgrade.logging(logging_step=x)
        def my_function_called_many_times(*args)

Try to fix : https://github.com/OCA/OpenUpgrade/issues/326

Regards.

CC : @pedrobaeza, @StefanRijnhart, @sebastienbeau, @OCA/openupgrade-maintainers

Fixes #967 by using `current_limit` instead of `current_rating` for checks. I think this might anyway be a better option.

@spauka and @sohailc, it would be nice if you could try this out on a real instrument (and please report your firmware revision!).

I'll try it out here in Copenhagen to see if my bold fixing claim is even true.

@Dominik-Vogel
